<h3><font color="blue">INTRODUCTION</font></h3>
<center><img src="file:///android_asset/bap/b plan(1)_resized.jpg" alt="b plan(1).jpg"/></center><br/>

<i>&quot;My intuition has always been starting with the customers and building something that optimizes not for 2-3 months but 2-3 years or even 20-30 years. And being convicted about those principles and being unwilling to stray from them is the difference between failure and success&quot;-Andrew Mason (founder of Groupon).</i><br><br>
<i>B-aptist</i> is the ultimate <b>b-plan event</b> where budding entrepreneurs can showcase those ideas which can become the next big business enterprise. For the first timers, here is a once-in-a-lifetime-opportunity to learn to properly translate your ideas in black and white and put a personal stamp on an existing idea. So put on your thinking caps and start looking for your idea!

<h3><font color="blue">Specifications</font></h3>
PRELIMS
<ul>
<li>Participants should submit an executive summary of their B&ndash;plan to baptist@tathva.org with the subject “B plan Executive Summary &lt;team name>”.</li>
<li>Last date for submission is 10 Oct 2013.</li>
<li>Based on the executive summary, a number of teams will be short-listed for the final round.
</ul><br/>
EXECUTIVE SUMMARY FORMAT:
</b>
<ul>
<li>The executive summary should be limited to a maximum of 1000 words (excluding index and introduction). Briefly state the purpose of the plan, opportunities, financial and marketing plans etc.</li>
<li>The document should be prepared in Times New Roman font, size 12 pt with 1.5 line spacing, submitted in pdf format.</li>
<li>The cover page of the abstract should contain names of the team members, college and contact details. The cover page will be detached before the papers are given to the panel evaluation. The name of the authors or the institutes should not appear anywhere in the body of the paper.</li>
<li>The business plan submitted should follow the provided format.</li>
</ul><br/>
FINAL PRESENTATION:
<ul><li>The shortlisted teams will present their B-plan in front of the judges in form of a presentation at Tathva 2013.</li>
<li>A maximum of 15 minutes will be given for the presentation. Points will be deducted for exceeding the time limit.</li>
<li>The presentation will follow a 10 minute question and answer round from the judges as well as the audience.</li>
<li>The decision taken by the judges would be final and participants will have to abide by it.</li>
</ul>


<h3><font color="blue">Prizes :</font></h3>
First Prize :Rs. 15000<br/>
Second Prize : Rs.10000<br/>
Third Prize : Rs.5000

<h3><font color="blue">No of participants</font></h3>
min : 1 <br>
max : 4

